  "texts": [
    "Mirroring the performance with missing data, Model 3 yields the most accurate forecasts.",
    "Notably, this model captures varying trends in the predicted years, unlike other models that predict a nearly constant rate across the entire forecast horizon.",
    "Finally, national incidence estimates are provided for each year in the time series.",
    "Results show that all models present low relative bias, generally around 1%, with Model 1 achieving the most accurate estimates overall.",
    "For short-term forecasting, Model 3 consistently demonstrates the lowest bias and narrowest credible intervals, achieving biases of 1.5%, 1.5%, and 1.4% for one-, two-, and three-year-ahead predictions, respectively."
